CrfPages.Name: Inclusion Criteria
CrfPages.Description: Who is eligible to apply to the study

Questions.QuestionText: The subject smokes > 9 cigarettes per day (average daily consumption during past month).
Questions.Name: INC[1]

Questions.QuestionText: The subject has smoked daily > 1 year
Questions.Name: INC[2]

Questions.QuestionText: The subject is motivated to quit smoking with the help of an alternative
Questions.Name: INC[3]

Questions.QuestionText: The subject is in good general health as evident by Medical History, physical examination, routine blood chemistry (Hb, total WBC, creatinine, electrolytes), and an ECG
Questions.Name: INC[4]

Questions.QuestionText: The subject practices, by self report, good oral hygiene (including brushing teeth) at least twice per day and having regular dental check ups
Questions.Name: INC[5]

Questions.QuestionText: The subject agrees to comply with the requirements of the protocol and complete study measures
Questions.Name: INC[7]

CrfPages.Name: Exclusion Criteria
CrfPages.Description: who is not eligible for study

Questions.QuestionText: The subject is a current user of ST (defined as daily usage during more than 1 week within past 6 months) or is unable to refrain from NRT or any other non-protocol treatment during the study. Use of pipes, cigars, cigarillos, snuff, and chewing tobacco is also prohibited during the study.
Questions.Name: EXC[0]

Questions.QuestionText: The subject is a female who is pregnant or lactating.
Questions.Name: EXC[1]

Questions.QuestionText: The subject has oral conditions that could potentially be made worse by use of study product, for instance, exposed dental cervices in the upper sulcus.
Questions.Name: EXC[2]

Questions.QuestionText: The subject has used any type of pharmaceutical (including some psychotropics, e.g., wellbutrin) or other products for smoking cessation within the past 3 months.
Questions.Name: EXC[3]

Questions.QuestionText: The subject has a history of clinically significant renal, hepatic, neurological, or chronic pulmonary disease that in the judgment of the investigator precludes participation.
Questions.Name: EXC[4]

Questions.QuestionText: The subject has a history of cardiovascular disease, including myocardial infarction within the last 3 months, significant cardiac arrhythmias, or poorly controlled hypertension (defined as a diastolic pressure of more than 90 mm Hg or a systolic pressure of more than 140 mm Hg) that in the judgment of the investigator precludes participation.
Questions.Name: EXC[5]

Questions.QuestionText: The subject has a history of alcohol or substance abuse or dependence other than cigarette smoking within the past year
Questions.Name: EXC[6]

Questions.QuestionText: Use of any illicit drug or smoked marijuana in the last 3 months.
Questions.Name: EXC[7]

Questions.QuestionText: The subject is unwilling to be randomized into active or placebo conditions, or be available for follow-up assessments.
Questions.Name: EXC[8]

Questions.QuestionText: The subject resides in a household where another member is currently participating in the study.
Questions.Name: EXC[9]

Questions.QuestionText: Did the subject attend the Information Session?
Questions.Name: IsAttended
